OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdenies backing UK strike   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Flaw                        
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The head of the UN's agency for        
OL,6, workers' rights has denied the         
OL,7, organisation backs the UK's tough new  
OL,8, anti-strike laws.                      
OL,10,FIt comes after UK ministers repeatedly 
OL,11,Fsuggested the International Labour     
OL,12,FOrganisation (ILO) supported government
OL,13,Fplans to enforce "minimum service      
OL,14,Flevels" during public sector strikes.  
OL,16,FThe new laws are meant to protect the  
OL,17,Fpublic from the impact of walkouts.    
OL,19,FBut unions have called them            
OL,20,F"undemocratic, unworkable and illegal".
